Quick comparison of which method to use:

| Method | Accuracy | Speed | Needs install |
|--------|----------|-------|---------------|
| `libreoffice` | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Closest to Word | Slow ~5-10s/file | `apt-get install libreoffice` |
| `python-docx` | ⭐⭐⭐ Good for structure | Fast ~0.1s/file | `pip install python-docx` |
| `both` | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Most strict | Slow | Both above |
| `auto` | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ Best available | Depends | Whatever is installed |

For GCP/AWS **LibreOffice is the closest thing to Word** you can get on Linux — it uses the same OOXML parser and will catch the same corruption Word catches.
